definition.value: This is an AE which is a form of bacterial meningitis.
This is an AE which is a viral disease caused by the mumps virus and complications include deafness and a wide range of inflammatory conditions, of which inflammation of the meninges.
This is an AE which is a serious medical condition in infants that is rapidly fatal if untreated.

This is an AE which continues to be associated with high rates of mortality and long-term neurological sequelae and the most common route of infection starts by nasopharyngeal colonization by Streptococcus pneumoniae, which must avoid mucosal entrapment and evade the host immune system after local activation.
This is an AE which is a symptomatic meningitis  infection caused by bacteria of the Salmonella type .
This is an AE which is a specific type of bacterial meningitis caused by the Mycobacterium tuberculosis infection of the meninges—the system of membranes which envelop the central nervous system.
This is an AE which is a type of meningitis due to a viral infection and it results in inflammation of the meninges.
This is an AE which is a birth defect in which there is incomplete closing of the spine and the membranes around the spinal cord during early development in pregnancy.
This is an AE which is a Gram-negative bacterium that can cause meningitis and other forms of meningococcal disease such as meningococcemia, a life-threatening sepsis.
This is an AE which describes infections caused by the bacterium Neisseria meningitidis.
This is an AE which is meningitis associated with herpes simplex virus (HSV).
This is an AE which is a birth defect in which there is incomplete closing of the spine and the membranes around the spinal cord during early development in pregnancy.
This is an AE which is a lysosomal storage disease which is commonly listed in the family of leukodystrophies as well as among the sphingolipidoses as it affects the metabolism of sphingolipids.
This is an AE which refers to any syndrome or disorder of mental function whose cause is alleged to be known as organic (physiologic) rather than purely of the mind.
This is an AE which is a fibrosing and inflammatory process, which involves the dura mater.
This is an AE which is a form of encephalomyopathy that is associated with a mitochondrial disease.
This is an AE which represents a syndrome of temporary or permanent disturbance of brain functions that occurs in different diseases and varies in clinical presentation.
This is an AE which is a hyperacute and frequently fatal form of ADEM.
This is an AE which is a form of hypoxia (reduced supply of oxygen), specifically involving the brain; when the brain is completely deprived of oxygen, it is called cerebral anoxia.
This is an AE which is a neural tube defect characterized by sac-like protrusions of the brain and the membranes that cover it through openings in the skull.
This is an AE which is a localized softening of the substance of the brain, due to bleeding or inflammation.
This is an AE which is inflammation of the brain and spinal cord.
This is an AE which is defined by signs and symptoms of abnormal neurological function in the first few days of life in an infant born at term.
This is an AE which is a type of encephalitis that can result from a number of autoimmune diseases.
This is an AE which defines as an illness characterized by myoclonus, ataxia, nystagmus, oculomotor palsies, and bulbar palsy in various combinations, with or without neuroimaging.
This is an AE which is discovered in Kern County, California and causes encephalitis in humans.
This is an AE which is an important opportunistic infection in HIV-infected patients but is rarely recognized in other groups.
This is an AE which is defined by the presence of an inflammatory process of the brain in association with clinical evidence of neurologic dysfunction caused by enteroviral.
This is an AE which is encephalitis due to herpes simplex virus.
This is an AE which is an infection of the brain caused by the Japanese encephalitis virus (JEV).
This is an AE which is an atypical form of encephalitis.
This is an AE which is a viral disease caused by the mumps virus and may occur encephalitis.
This is an AE which is inflammation of the brain parenchyma, called encephalitis, by a virus.
This is an AE which is a brain injury in which scattered lesions occur over a widespread area in white matter tracts as well as grey matter.
This is an AE which is a rare endocrine condition featuring a low blood sodium concentration and dehydration in response to injury (trauma) or the presence of tumors in or surrounding the brain.
This is an AE which is a head injury that temporarily affects brain functioning.
This is an AE which is the pathologic process that results in an area of necrotic tissue in the brain (cerebral infarct) with embolic.
This is an AE which is a neurological condition characterized by encephalopathy, thyroid autoimmunity, and good clinical response to corticosteroids.
This is an AE which is a cephalic disorder in which the prosencephalon (the forebrain of the embryo) fails to develop into two hemispheres.

This is an AE which is the common collective name for human betaherpesvirus 6A (HHV-6A) and human betaherpesvirus 6B (HHV-6B) and can be associated with encephalitis in the case of immunocompromised patients.

This is an AE which is a syndrome (a set of signs and symptoms) with encephalomyelitis that is the consequence of cancer in the body, specifically due to the production of chemical signaling molecules (such as hormones or cytokines) by tumor cells or by an immune response against the tumor.
This is an AE which can result from neonatal encephalopathy and perinatal arterial ischaemic stroke, usually at term, but also in preterm infants.
This is an AE which is a form of white-matter brain injury, characterized by the necrosis (more often coagulation) of white matter near the lateral ventricles.
This is an AE which is a set of symptoms that may continue for weeks, months, or a year or more after a concussion – a mild form of traumatic brain injury (TBI).

This is an AE which is a neurologic disorder caused by exposure to neurotoxic organic solvents such as toluene, following exposure to heavy metals such as manganese, as a side effect of melarsoprol treatment for African trypanosomiasis, adverse effects to prescription drugs, or exposure to extreme concentrations of any natural toxin such as cyanotoxins found in shellfish or freshwater cyanobacteria crusts.

This is an AE which is a rare condition that is characterized by progressive damage (-pathy) to white matter (-leuko-) in the brain (-encephalo-), particularly myelin, due to causes such as exposure to substance use, environmental toxins, or chemotherapeutic drugs.
This is an AE which is a hyperacute and frequently fatal form of acute disseminated encephalomyelitis(ADEM).
This is an AE which is an acute inflammation of the protective membranes covering the brain and spinal cord caused by adenoviral.
This is an AE which is rare but well recognised entity usually manifesting 1-4 weeks after anoxic exposure and characteristic subcortical white matter demyelination with necrosis of globus pallidus.

This is an AE which is a structural defect in the cerebellum, characterized by a downward displacement of one or both cerebellar tonsils through the foramen magnum (the opening at the base of the skull).
